:::summary
Christianity is the world's largest religion — the faith of more than two billion people — and the spiritual, moral, and intellectual foundation of Western civilization. It is centered on the person and work of **Jesus Christ**: his birth in Bethlehem, his ministry in Galilee and Judea, his crucifixion and bodily resurrection in Jerusalem, and his promise to return. Christians believe that Jesus is the eternal Son of God who became human for our salvation — that in his death the debt of human sin was paid and in his resurrection the power of death was broken — and that all who trust in him receive forgiveness, new life, and the hope of eternal glory.
:::

